The paper focuses on regularization of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the potential applications of their proposed method in different areas of artificial intelligence, which suggests that it could also be relevant to "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments conducted in the paper involve various types of network architecture and image datasets, indicating that it could be related to "cs.CV" (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the convergence rates of their proposed method, which suggests that it could be relevant to "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a novel regularizer for improving generalization of DNNs, which could be relevant to "cs.SY" (Systems and Control).
